cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.HC 

This paper uses recurrent neural networks to analyze unstructured text conversation in customer service chat logs to infer customer satisfaction. This falls under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the practical implications of their findings for customer service departments, which could fall under social and information networks (cs.SI) or human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper touches on biases in online rating platforms, which could fall under cryptography and security (cs.CY).
